org.openliberty.openaz.azapi.constants
Enum PepResponseBehavior

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<PepResponseBehavior>
      org.openliberty.openaz.azapi.constants.PepResponseBehavior
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<PepResponseBehavior>
public enum PepResponseBehavior
extends java.lang.Enum<PepResponseBehavior>

This enum provides the options that can be set using the PepResponseFactory to determine the behavior when PepResponse.allowed() is called AND the AzDecision is either Indeterminate or NotApplicable.

The different conditions for which behavior is specified and which ones can be configured are the following:

  • AzDecision.AZ_PERMIT allowed() always returns true
  • AzDecision.AZ_DENY allowed() always returns false
  • AzDecision.AZ_NOTAPPLICABLE allowed() is configurable with default behavior being RETURN_NO
  • AzDecision.AZ_INDETERMINATE has specific AzStatusCode values, each of which is configurable as follows:
    • AzStatusCode.AZ_MISSING_ATTRIBUTE allowed() has default behavior: RETURN_NO
    • AzStatusCode.AZ_PROCESSING_ERROR allowed() has default behavior: THROW_EXCEPTION
    • AzStatusCode.AZ_SYNTAX_ERROR allowed() has default behavior: THROW_EXCEPTION

Author:
Josh Bregman, Rich Levinson, Prateek Mishra
